---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Cloud Migration Intelligence" description="VScalar cloud migration intelligence — discovery, dependency mapping, move group design, firewall analysis, network integration, and architecture.">

  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Cloud Migration</p>
    <h1>Cloud Migration Intelligence</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      VScalar helps enterprises move beyond static inventories and spreadsheet-based migration
      planning by bringing together infrastructure intelligence, application context, dependency
      relationships, network paths, firewall requirements, and architecture decisions into a
      unified migration workflow.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="large-text">
      The focus is not just moving workloads from one environment to another. It is understanding
      how enterprise transformations actually happen — technically, operationally, and organizationally.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section light">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:#0284c7;">End-to-End Workflow</p>
    <h2>Cloud Migration Phases</h2>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>1. Discovery &amp; Assessment</h3>
        <p>Collect and assess infrastructure inventories, technology stacks, ownership, lifecycle status, readiness indicators, and migration scope across enterprise environments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>2. Application Dependency Mapping</h3>
        <p>Identify application, infrastructure, database, service, and communication relationships to support impact analysis and dependency-aware migration planning.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>3. Move Group Design</h3>
        <p>Design migration waves and move groups based on dependencies, business criticality, environment, complexity, risk, and transformation priorities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>4. Firewall Rule Analysis</h3>
        <p>Analyze observed communication paths, source and destination relationships, ports, protocols, and security policies required for migration planning.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>5. Migration Strategy</h3>
        <p>Support workload-level migration decisions — rehost, replatform, refactor, retain, retire, or modernize — based on technical and business context.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>6. Network Integration</h3>
        <p>Assess routing, hybrid connectivity, SD-WAN paths, DNS, segmentation, transit architectures, and cloud communication requirements.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>7. Architecture &amp; Landing Zone Design</h3>
        <p>Guide target-state architecture decisions for landing zones, identity, security, HA/DR, backup, monitoring, governance, and operational readiness.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>8. Migration Execution &amp; Cutover Support</h3>
        <p>Support migration readiness, runbook planning, cutover coordination, validation, issue tracking, and decision visibility across migration waves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:#0284c7;">Platform Capabilities</p>
    <h2>What the Platform Does</h2>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Inventory Intelligence</h3>
        <p>Discovery and assessment of infrastructure assets across data centers, virtualization platforms, cloud environments, storage, network, and CMDB sources. Identifies ownership, technology stacks, readiness indicators, and migration scope.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Application Dependency Mapping</h3>
        <p>Identification of application, infrastructure, database, service, and communication relationships. Supports impact analysis, dependency-aware planning, and understanding of how workloads actually operate.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Move Group Design</h3>
        <p>Planning of migration waves and move groups based on dependencies, business criticality, environment, complexity, and risk. Helps reduce cutover risk and avoid breaking application relationships.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Firewall Intelligence</h3>
        <p>Analysis of security policies, observed communication flows, ports, protocols, and migration-related firewall requirements. Supports rule rationalization and cloud security planning.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Network Intelligence</h3>
        <p>Assessment of routing, hybrid connectivity, SD-WAN paths, DNS, segmentation, and cloud communication requirements. Identifies network dependencies that often block or delay migration execution.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Cloud Compute Sizing</h3>
        <p>Assessment of workload sizing, utilization, target cloud capacity, right-sizing opportunities, and migration target planning across cloud compute platforms.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Cloud Design Patterns</h3>
        <p>Guidance for landing zones, HA/DR, backup, monitoring, identity, connectivity, security patterns, and migration architecture decisions across migration programs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>AI-Assisted Decision Support</h3>
        <p>AI-assisted summarization, reasoning, recommendations, and design guidance using enterprise context. Helps architects and migration teams improve decision quality while keeping expert judgment in the loop.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="platform">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:#78d6ff;">Walkthrough</p>
    <h2>Platform Walkthrough</h2>
    <p>
      A recorded walkthrough will demonstrate how VScalar analyzes synthetic enterprise datasets
      to assess inventory, identify dependencies, design move groups, analyze firewall requirements,
      support network planning, and guide cloud migration decisions.
    </p>
    <p>
      The public site does not expose a live demo environment. Enterprise migration data is sensitive,
      and the platform walkthrough is designed to show the workflow and outputs without exposing
      real customer data.
    </p>
    <div class="buttons" style="margin-top:28px;">
      <a class="btn secondary" href="/contact">Request Demo</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
